  "text": "the term salvage surgery is not clearly defined and has been used variously to describe a second attempt at cure after definite treatment or the final attempt for cure in case of recurrent disease following previous surgery, previous rt or rCt or a combination of the options mentioned. In HNSCC, salvage surgery is often the only curative option available and is mainly performed as the final curative attempt. the term salvage surgery is currently also used incorrectly for elective surgery following initial treatment and for persistent disease following an initial treatment attempt [CITATION_1] .",
